%% Data Science Pipelines - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Dashboard
    participant UI as ml-pipeline-ui<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant API as ml-pipeline<br/>(API Server)<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as MinIO/S3<br/>9000/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as MySQL/PostgreSQL<br/>3306/TCP
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow<br/>Controller
    participant StepPod as Pipeline Step Pod<br/>(driver + launcher)
    participant MLMD as metadata-grpc-server<br/>8080/TCP gRPC
    participant PA as Persistence Agent
    participant SWC as Scheduled Workflow<br/>Controller
    participant Cache as cache-server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,MLMD: Flow 1: Pipeline Submission and Execution

    User->>UI: Submit pipeline run<br/>kubeflow-userid header
    UI->>API: POST /apis/v2beta1/runs<br/>Bearer Token
    API->>S3: Store pipeline spec<br/>Access Key auth
    API->>DB: Persist run metadata<br/>Username/Password
    API->>K8s: Create Workflow CR<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8s->>Argo: Workflow CR created
    Argo->>K8s: Create step pod

    Note over K8s,Cache: Flow 4: Cache Check (Admission Webhook)

    K8s->>Cache: Mutating webhook call<br/>TLS, K8s API mTLS
    Cache->>DB: Check cache entry<br/>Username/Password
    Cache-->>K8s: Allow/Modify pod<br/>(skip if cached)

    Argo->>StepPod: Start driver container
    StepPod->>StepPod: Driver resolves inputs,<br/>creates sub-DAGs
    StepPod->>StepPod: Launcher executes<br/>user container
    StepPod->>S3: Upload artifacts<br/>Access Key auth
    StepPod->>MLMD: Record execution metadata<br/>gRPC (no auth)
    StepPod-->>Argo: Step complete

    Note over PA,API: Flow 2: Persistence Agent State Sync

    PA->>K8s: Watch Workflow CRs<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8s-->>PA: Workflow status update
    PA->>API: Sync run state<br/>8888/TCP or 8887/TCP<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over SWC,K8s: Flow 3: Scheduled Workflow Execution

    SWC->>K8s: Watch ScheduledWorkflow CRs<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8s-->>SWC: ScheduledWorkflow trigger
    SWC->>K8s: Create Workflow CR<br/>ServiceAccount Token
